  "text": "The protein used was a double mutant of the I27 domain from human cardiac titin, where both cysteine residues were mutated to serines, which will be referred to as I27 in this paper. (I27) [CITATION_1] polyprotein constructs were expressed and purified according to methods described previously [CITATION_2] . All domains in the protein constructs were assumed to be folded under the conditions used in the AFM experiments, based on characterization of the stability of (I27) 5 described elsewhere [CITATION_3] .",
